    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Fugitive organic blue colorant obtained from cornflower petals (Centaurea dyanus); used in some 18th-century watercolor paintings.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000047822/MFA Conservation and Art Material Encyclopedia Online: CAMEO (2005-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Vergankelijk organisch blauw kleurmiddel dat wordt verkregen uit het bloemblad van de korenbloem (Centaurea dyanus). Werd gebruikt in bepaalde 18e-eeuwse aquarellen.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>取自矢車菊（Centaurea cyanus）花瓣，易褪色的有機藍色著色劑。某些十八世紀的水彩畫曾經使用。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
